Pictures  and  Legendary Picturesโ โDune,โ the big-screen adaptation of Frank Herbertโs seminal bestseller of the same name. A mythic and emotionally charged heroโs journey, โDuneโ tells the story of Paul Atreides, a brilliant and gifted young man born into a great destiny beyond his understanding, who must travel to the most dangerous planet  in  the  universe  to  ensure  the  future  of  his  family  and  his  people. Villeneuve directed โDuneโ from a screenplay he co-wrote with Jon Spaihts and Eric Roth based on the novel of the same name written by Frank Herbert.  Villeneuve also produced the film with Mary Parent, Cale Boyter  and  Joe  Caracciolo,  Jr.   The  executive  producers  are  Tanya  Lapointe,  Joshua  Grode,  Herbert  W.  Gains, Jon Spaihts, Thomas Tull, Brian Herbert, Byron Merritt and Kim Herbert. He  also  collaborated  for  the  first  time  with  Oscar-nominated  director  of  photography  Greig  Fraser  (โLion,โ  โZero  Dark  Thirty,โ  โRogue  One:  A  Star  Wars  Storyโ);  three-time  Oscar-nominated  costume  designer  Jacqueline West (โThe Revenant,โ โThe Curious Case of Benjamin Button,โ โQuillsโ) and co-costume designer Bob Morgan; and stunt coordinator Tom Struthers (โThe Dark Knightโ trilogy, โInceptionโ).
